default&#xa0;default1.1.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultNational Grid owns and manages the grids to which many different energy sources are connected. In 
defaultBritain
default we run systems that deliver gas and electricity across the entire country. We hold a vital position at the centre of the energy system. We join everything up.
default&#xa0;
default1.2.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultNational Grid is at the heart of one of the greatest challenges 
defaultfor the 
defaultUK
default energy industry - to
default deliver low carbon energy in an affordable, secure and sustainable way. This is an industry wide challenge that will require an estimated £200 billion of investment up to 2020 to transform the UK’s energy infrastructure
default, 
defaulte
defaultnsuring the development of an energy system that can underpin our economic prosperity in the 21st century.  
