default&#xa0;default7.1.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThere is a comprehensive gas distribution network within the UK, a long life reliable asset that supplies heat economically to most domestic consumers. Replacing the gas network with a community heat network has
default 
defaultn
defaulto
defaultt made economic sense for most pl
defaultaces in the UK. The exception to this are places with low cost sources of recovered heat that can supply heat to heat networks at a competitive rate. Our analysis of heat networks suggests that there is a role for industrial and commercial sectors where it
default is possible to cluster businesses that could use the recovered heat from industrial processes and thermal power stations. For example, the heat pipe that takes recovered heat from Eon’s Isle of Grain power station to be used at National Grid’s Isle of Gra
defaultin LNG terminal.
default default&#xa0;default&#xa0;default8.1.
default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThe RHI currently only promotes ground source heat
default 
defaultpumps in commercial applications
default,
default and is due to apply for residential properties from March 2014 so it is too early to tell whether it promotes heat pumps successfully. 
