default10.2.
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThermal storage is more likely to provide diurnal storage, similar to the gas network or a hot water tank today, as it tends to be at the point of use and this has some system benefits in managing the within day heat load.  However seasonal storage
default of energy, not just heat, could create greater value as it would mitigate the seasonal impact of heat demand, and reduce the need for increased network and generator capacity to electrify heat, research into technologies that could provide this would be o
defaultf value.
